The Municipality is also involved in other international networks as 100 Resilient Cities and C-40. &#xd;
100 Resilient Cities was created by the Rockefeller Foundation and aims not only to help individual cities become more resilient, but will facilitate the building of a global practice of resilience among governments, NGOs, the private sector, and individual citizens. &#xd;
Working across multiple sectors and issues, C40 convenes networks that provide a range of services in support of citiesâ€™ climate change efforts. C40 currently has 17 networks that cover the mitigation, adaptation and sustainability topics of highest priority to C40 cities and with the potential for the greatest climate impact. C40 networks help cities replicate, improve and accelerate climate action&#xd;
Here you can find the websites:&#xd;
https://www.100resilientcities.org/&#xd;
